p: Fatty acid methyl ester’s (FAME’s) derivatives were identified and quantified by GC-FID. Values of ∑SFAs (total saturated fatty acids) were 14.1% for p-menthane and 14.9% for n-hexane. Amounts of ∑MUFAs (total mono-unsaturated fatty acids) were 61.1% for p-menthane and 58.1% for n-hexane, while those for ∑PUFAs (poly-unsaturated fatty acids) were 26.6% for p-menthane and 26.0% for n-hexane.
